                                                                       Collision Resolution 


Collision kya hoti hai?
Jab do ya zyada different keys ka hash same index (bucket) par aa jaye.
hash(k1) % n = 5
hash(k2) % n = 5   ← collision

🛠️ Collision Resolution Techniques :
1️⃣ Open Addressing (Closed Hashing) ?
Collision hone par same table ke kisi aur empty slot me element rakhte hain.
     🔹 Iske types hote hain: 
                  (a) Linear Probing :- 
                         - Simple next slot check karo.
                         - Index = (hash value + i) % tableSize  => i = kitni baar tum next slot try kar rahe ho (i = 0,i = 1,i = 2)
                         - Probe Number :- collision ane ke bad jitna steps hmne include kiya hai  khali slot ke liye wo hmara probe number bn jata hai isko 1 se count krte na ki 0 se.
                         - ❌ Problem: Clustering (continuous block ban jata hai). there are two types of clustring : Primary and secondry clustring.
                  (b) Quadratic Probing :-
                         - Gap increase hota hai (i²)
                         - Index = (hash + i²) % n
                         - ✔ Clustering kam hota hai.
                  (c) Double Hashing :-
                         - Second hash function use karte hain.
                         - Index = (h1(key) + i * h2(key)) % n.
                         - ✔ Best distribution
                         - ✔ Clustering almost nahi hota
       ❓ Agar probing ke baad bhi jagah na mile to?
           👉 Tab sirf probing continue nahi karte…Hum rehashing (resize) karte hain, jo load factor pe depend karta hai.
            🔹 Load Factor kya hota hai?
                - Load factor batata hai ki hash table kitna fill ho chuka hai.
                                              Number of elements​
                - Formula:  Load Factor (α) = --------------------
                                                Table Size
                - 🔴 Problem kab hoti hai?
                           - Jab load factor se zyada ho jata hai (table almost full).
                           - Linear probing me:
                                           - ❌ Bahut zyada probing lagega
                                           - ❌ Clustering badhega
                                           - ❌ Performance O(n) ho sakta hai.
                - 🚀 Solution → Rehashing :
                    👉 Jab load factor threshold cross kare (like 0.7 / 0.75)
                                          - Naya bada array banao (generally 2x size)
                                          - Saare old elements ko dubara insert karo
                                          - New hash calculate hoga (kyunki size change hua)
     🔥 Open Addressing me Deletion kaise krte hai ?
        - 👉 (Linear / Quadratic / Double hashing me),Direct delete kyu nahi kar sakte.
        - Steps :
               - Key find karo (probing se).
               - Direct remove mat karo.
               - Usko mark karo → DELETED.
        - Explanation :
               - Maan lo:
                         Index:   5   6   7
                         Data:   [A] [B] [C]
                         Aur B delete kar diya (index 6 empty kar diya).
                         [A] [ _ ] [C]
                         👉 Ab problem 👇
                                      C ka search karoge
                                      hash = 5 → 5 pe A mila
                                      next 6 → empty mila ❌
                                                     Search stop ho jayega ❌
                                                     C mil hi nahi payega
               - ✅ Solution: "Lazy Deletion" (Tombstone concept) 
                         Direct empty nahi karte, Ek special mark laga dete hain: DELETED
                         [A] [DEL] [C]

2️⃣ Closed Addressing (Separate Chaining) ?
Same index pe multiple elements store karte hain.
✔ Har bucket me:
LinkedList / Tree
Example: Index 5 → [k1 → k2 → k3]
✔ Simple
✔ No clustering issue
⚔️ Open vs Closed Hashing
| Feature   | Open Addressing | Separate Chaining |
| --------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| Storage   | Same array      | LinkedList/Tree   |
| Space     | Less            | More              |
| Collision | New slot        | Same bucket       |
| Example   | Linear probing  | HashMap           |

Note:-
🔥 Java me kya use hota hai?
